And as they were coming down the mountain, Jesus charged them, saying, "Do not tell anyone what you have seen until the Son of Man has risen from the dead."
And his disciples asked him, saying, "Why do the scribes say that Elijah must come first?"
Then Jesus answered and said unto them, Elijah shall first come, and restore all things.
But I tell you, Elijah has already come, and they did not recognize him, but they treated him as they pleased. So the Son of Man will also suffer at their hands."
Then the disciples understood that he spake unto them of John the Baptist. For he had cast out a devil from a man that was possessed with him.
And when they came to the assembly, a man came forward and prostrated himself before him.
Saying, "Lord, have mercy on my son, for he is convulsing and in great pain, often falling into fire and often into water."
And he brought him to his disciples, but they could not heal him."
Then Jesus answered and said, "O unbelieving and perverse generation, how long shall I be with you? How long shall I put up with you? Bring him here to me!"
Jesus rebuked him, and the devil departed out of him. And from that hour the boy was made whole.
Then the disciples came to Jesus in private and said, "Why couldn't we cast him out?"
Then Jesus said to them, "Because of your lack of faith. Truly I tell you, if you have faith as small as a mustard seed, you can say to this mountain, 'Move from here to there,' and it will move; nothing will be impossible for you."
"As for this religion, it can only be achieved through prayer and fasting."
And as they were uncertain in Galilee, Jesus said to them, "The Son of Man is to be delivered into the hands of men."
They killed him, and on the third day he will rise. And they were very sorrowful. The tax of the temple.
And when they came to Capernaum, those who collected the two drachmas came to Peter and said, "Does your teacher not pay the two drachmas?"
He said, "Yes." And when he entered the house, Jesus went before him, saying, "Simon, what do you think? From whom do the kings of the earth collect tribute or customs, from their own children or from strangers?"
Peter said to him, "The foreigners." Jesus said to him, "If the sons are free.
But lest we offend them, go to the sea and cast your line; and whatever comes up first, take it, and when it opens its mouth, you will find a shekel; take that and give it to them for me and for you."
